</header><div class="" id="content"><section class="textBox s0 last prev- next- back-default htop- hbottom-" id="textBox0"><div class="site"><div class="entry layout-default"><span class="title-rap"><h1 class="title">Privacy Policy
</h1></span><div class="text"><p>Thank you for visiting <a href="https://nanolocksecurity.com/">https://nanolocksecurity.com/</a> (the “<strong>Website</strong>“). This privacy policy (the “<strong>Policy</strong>“) explains the information we collect¸ how we use the information¸ some of the security steps taken to protect the information¸ and the choices you have to review or revise such information. This Policy forms a part of our Terms of Use¸ available at: <a href="https://nanolocksecurity.com/Privacy">https://nanolocksecurity.com/Privacy</a> (the “<strong>Terms</strong>“)¸ and is incorporated thereto by reference. The definitions in our Terms apply to this Privacy Policy unless stated otherwise.</p>
<p>If you have any objections to this Privacy¸ you should immediately discontinue use of the website.</p>
<p><strong>What information do we collect and how do we use it?</strong></p>
<p>Nanolock Security does not collect any personal or identifiable information about its Website’s visitors. We do however collect Non-Personal Information (as described below) from our visitors for a variety of reasons¸ including as part of our ongoing efforts to provide superior visitor experience. We also monitor site use and traffic patterns to improve our website design and performance. You may also willingly provide us with your email addresses in order to send you messages.</p>
<p><strong>Non-Personal Information</strong></p>
<p>When you interact with us via the Website we receive and store certain personally non-identifiable information. We track this information either directly or through a third-party tracking service. Such information¸ which is collected passively using various technologies¸ cannot presently be used to specifically identify you. Nanolock Security may store such information itself or such information may be included in databases owned and maintained by Nanolock Security’s affiliates¸ agents or service providers. The website may use such information and pool it with other information from the Website to track¸ for example¸ the total number of visitors to our website¸ the number of visitors to each page of our Website¸ the domain names of our visitors’ Internet service providers¸ and how our users use and interact with the Website. Nanolock Security may share this non-identifiable and aggregate data with its affiliates¸ agents and business partners¸ but this type of non-identifiable and aggregate information does not identify you personally. Nanolock Security may also disclose aggregated user statistics in order to describe our Website to current and prospective business partners and to other third parties for other lawful purposes.</p>
<p><strong>Security</strong></p>
<p>Nanolock Security takes reasonable steps to protect the information provided via the Website from loss¸ misuse¸ and unauthorized access¸ disclosure¸ alteration¸ or destruction. However¸ no internet¸ email or other electronic transmission is ever fully secure or error free¸ so you should take special care in deciding what information you send to us in this way.</p>
<p><strong>Disclosure of Information</strong></p>
<p>We may disclose information to other members of the Nanolock Security corporate family and our business partners. We will also disclose information as we determine to be required by law.</p>
